				\begin{document}$${{{\mathrm{NO}}}}_3^ -$$\end{document} > Br− > Cl− > F− > OH−. Therefore, it is obvious that nitrate ions are displaced quite easier, hence they are the utmost proper precursors for the fabrication of LDHs via anion-exchange route89. Furthermore, this technique involves the synthesis of LDHs with host anions using a co-precipitation approach, then exchanging with the guest anions. This approach is only applied when the co-precipitation approach is improper, like the unstable di- or tri-valent metal cations or anions in basic conditions90. In general, the mechanism of the anion-exchange reaction can be expressed as follows:7LDH.Am−+Xn−→LDH.Xn−+Am−\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
